summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming resolutions 733 (1992) and 751 (1992), 
Expressing desire for peace and security in Somalia,
Recognizing UN efforts to deliver humanitarian assistance,
Acting under Chapter VII,
1. Reiterates obligation to comply with arms embargo imposed by resolution 733 (1992) and urges States to ensure full implementation;
2. Exempts protective clothing, including flak jackets and helmets, for UN personnel, media, humanitarian and development workers for personal use;
3. Exempts non-lethal military equipment for humanitarian or protective use, approved by the Committee established by resolution 751 (1992);
4. Requests Committee to consider and decide on exemption requests;
5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
